{{Politics of Malta}}
A referendum on a [[Constitution of Malta|new constitution]] was held in [[Malta]] between 2 and 4 May 1964.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p1302 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> It was approved by 54.5% of voters, and came into effect on 21 September 1964. It was effectively a [[independence referendum|referendum on independence]], as the new constitution gave the country self-government.
==Question== The question put to the electorate was "Do you approve of the constitution proposed by the Government of Malta, endorsed by the Legislative Assembly, and published in the Malta Gazette?<ref>[http://www.maltadata.com/ref-votes.htm Referenda in Malta: The Questions and the Voters' Responses] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927101516/http://www.maltadata.com/ref-votes.htm |date=2011-09-27 }} Elections in Malta</ref>
==Results== {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right !Choice !Votes !% |- |align=left|For||65,714||54.5 |- |align=left|Against||54,919||45.5 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes||9,016||– |- |align=left|'''Total'''||'''129,649'''||'''100''' |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout||162,743||79.7 |- |align=left colspan=3|Source: Nohlen & Stöver |}
