The '''Ministry of Justice, Transparency and Human Rights''' ({{lang-el|Υπουργείο Δικαιοσύνης, Διαφάνειας και Ανθρωπίνων Δικαιωμάτων}}) is the [[ministry (government department)|government department]] entrusted with the supervision of the [[civil law (legal system)|legal]] and [[judicial system of Greece|judicial system]] of [[Greece]]. Current minister is the independent [[Nikos Paraskevopoulos]].
It was founded as the '''State Secretariat for Justice''' ({{lang|grc|Ἡ ἐπὶ τῆς Δικαιοσύνης Γραμματεία τῆς Ἐπικρατείας}}) in April 1833, and later known as the '''Ministry of Justice''' ({{lang|el|Υπουργείο Δικαιοσύνης}}). It received its current name in October 2009 under prime minister [[George Papandreou]].
