{{Politics of Nagorno Karabakh}}
A '''constitutional referendum''' was held in the [[List of unrecognized countries|unrecognised country]] of [[Nagorno-Karabakh Republic|Nagorno-Karabakh]] on 10 December 2006 to approve a draft [[constitution]],<ref>[http://www.defacto.am/index.php?OP=71319645 www.defacto.am<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> which defined Nagorno-Karabakh as a sovereign state.<ref> [http://www.panarmenian.net/news/eng/?nid=20271 Karabakh Ahead of Many Neighboring States on Democratic Values], ''[[Pan-Armenian]]'', 2006-12-04 </ref> [[Azerbaijan]] condemned the referendum, saying it is an unconstitutional attempt to damage the peace process. <ref> [http://www.today.az/news/politics/33428.html Constitution referendum in Nagorno Karabakh is aimed at damaging peace process], ''Today.AZ'', 2006-12-02 </ref>
The constitution was approved by 99.28% of voters, with a turnout of 87%.<ref>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=az012006 Berg-Karabach (Aserbeidschan), 10. Dezember 2006 : Verfassung] Direct Democracy</ref>
