'''PlayStation mentality''' refers to the disassociation between combatants and the consequences of their actions, as a result of the use of weapon interfaces which resemble [[video games]].  The effect is named after the [[PlayStation]] games console, and is commonly cited in discussions of the problems of [[drone strike|drone warfare]], such as that conducted by the [[CIA]] in the [[Drone attacks in Pakistan|Pakistan tribal areas]], typically using [[predator drones]].

